##Redesivir, how close is it to becoming the new crown wonder drug?

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

* News of a new coronary pneumonia patient being cured with Radcivir has spread a lot of news about the drug's "miraculous effect" , but it is only "good wishes" .
* With the number of confirmed, suspected, and dead cases of coronary pneumonia rising, hope is desperately needed.
* DECIVOR's previous generation of drugs has been shown to be effective in the treatment of feline faecal transmission caused by the cat coronavirus. As a result, some people even hope to buy this cat medicine to the new coronary pneumonia patients.
* Example does not speak for itself. Two clinical trials of Radcivir in patients with new-onset pneumonia are under way, and whether it works or not will not be known until the end of the trial.
* Until a cure is found, the best hope for patients with NCP is their own immunity.

News that a new U. S. patient with coronary pneumonia was cured with Radcivir has prompted much talk of the drug's "miraculous effects, " but only "wishful thinking. ".

The number of confirmed, suspected, and dead cases of new coronary pneumonia is on the rise, and hope is desperately needed.

A previous generation of Ridgeway has been shown to be effective in the treatment of Feline coronavirus-induced Venereal Disease. As a result, some people even hope to buy this cat medicine to the new coronary pneumonia patients.

Isolated cases don't speak for themselves. Two clinical trials of Radcivir in patients with new-onset pneumonia are under way, and whether it works or not will not be known until the end of the trial.

Until a cure is found, the best hope for patients with NCP is their own immunity.

This weekend, news of Ridgeway's "miracle effect" on patients with new-onset pneumonia again caught the attention of social media.

On February 8th, a patient who claimed to have been admitted to Wuhan's Jinyintan Hospital sent a message: "The American cow with the new drug redoxivir really, after watching it eat for a day with the critically ill patients in the ward, has visibly improved, and now sits and chats with me in good spirits. " It got a lot of retweets and comments.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Screenshot via Weibo

This information looks promising, but it's unfortunately as if, as previously claimed from various sources, "recovering 96% of lung function in 17 hours from ICU status" , "random blind screening, all 700 outcomes" , it's more likely to be wishful thinking. For one thing, ridgway is an injection, not a "pill. " For another, in a double-blind trial, neither the doctor nor the patient would know whether the drug was a placebo or a real drug.

Since a paper published online Jan. 31 in the respected Medical Journal The New England Journal of Medicine, describing the role of the unmarketed drug Redesavir in the treatment of the first patient in the United States to be diagnosed with NCP, there's been a lot of talk about it.

The number of confirmed, suspected, and dead cases of new coronary pneumonia is on the rise, and hope is desperately needed. Remdesivir has even been transliterated as "the hope of the people" .

So far, however, there has been only one success story in the United States, and one alone does not tell the story. Wang Chen, vice president of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and President of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, said at the launch of the clinical trial on Feb. 5 that expectations had been raised, but that rigorous scientific results would have to be awaited to see if the trial would be effective.

So, can Ridgeville be a wonder drug? How close is it to actually becoming "the hope of the people" ?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: yestone

##What kind of clinical trial results are considered successful?

On Feb. 9, a search for the keyword "Remdesivir" entered on the official website of the American clinical trial database showed that three clinical studies were under way: a Phase III RCT trial (Randomized controlled trial) for patients with mild to moderate new coronary pneumonia, completion is expected on April 27; a Phase III RCT trial for patients with severe new pneumonia is expected on May 1.

Another trial, conducted by U.S. researchers at the Zaire Ebolavirus, began on Oct. 25,2018, and is expected to finish on Nov. 30 at the 2023.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The two studies will include 308 mild to moderate cases and 452 severe cases, all randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, multicenter studies, according to the American clinical trial database.

Unlike the traditional 1:1 grouping of patients (one group for treatment and one group for control) in a clinical trial for severe new coronary pneumonia, the split was 2:1, meaning participants had a 67 percent chance of taking the drug, Xinhua reported.

The two studies had different criteria for success in clinical trials. In Clinical Studies evaluating mild / moderate patients, the main outcome measures were remission within the prescribed time window (28 days) . The main outcome measures were:

FEVER: axillary temperature ≤36.6 °C, oral temperature ≤37.2 °C, anal temperature or ear temperature ≤37.8 °C
Frequency of inhalation: ≤24 times / Min (Indoor Air)
OXYGENATION: 94% (under indoor air)
COUGH: mild or no (cough is classified as "severe / Moderate / Mild / No")

Frequency of inhalation: ≤24 times / Min (Indoor Air)

OXYGENATION: 94% (under indoor air)

In a trial to assess the clinical outcome in critically ill patients, the patient's clinical assessment was reduced by two grades within a prescribed time window (28 days) , with a six-grade clinical assessment as follows:

6. Death
5. Need ECMO (artificial membrane lung) or IMV (invasive mechanical ventilation) in ICU;
4. Intensive Care Unit / Inpatient Care Requiring Niv (non-invasive Mechanical Ventilation) / HFNC (High Flow Nasal Cannula) ;
3. Hospitalization with supplemental oxygen (but without Niv / HFNC) ;
2. Hospitalization Without Supplemental Oxygen;
1. Discharge from hospital.

During the prescribed time window (28 days) , patients with mild to moderate illness who were treated with Radzivir experienced remission in terms of fever and Oxygenation, or patients with severe illness experienced a 2-step decline in clinical evaluation, a significant statistical difference between the two groups of patients who were given a placebo would be considered a success.

##Why is Ridgeway considered a "wonder drug" ?

In addition to having a successful treatment, Ridgeville is expected to have a long and complex history, with many trials investigating its activity and safety.

Zhao Yong (not his real name) , a drug researcher living abroad, recently received a special request from a woman in Wuhan who wanted him to buy a cat drug codenamed GS-441524 for her family instead of cats. Her father had died of new coronary pneumonia, as had her aunt and grandfather, and she hoped the drug would save their lives.

GS-441524 has not yet been approved for sale and has no trade name, but it does not affect the obscure scientific term's reputation in the cat world as a FelineInfectious Feline Infectious Peritonitis, with a cure rate of more than 90 per cent.

But why would this woman want to use cat drugs on people? Cat-to-cat transmission is a disease caused by a mutation of the cat coronavirus carried by the cat. "It's all coronavirus infection, and the mechanism is the same, " Zhao said.

In 2012, Gilead published a report on the key compound, GS-441524, which showed broad antiviral activity against influenza a, human influenza and SARS-CoV. Some veterinary scientists have found GS-441524 to be very effective in treating venereal disease in cats.

Feline transmissible venereal disease is a lethal abnormal immune response that occurs in cats and is caused by mutations in the feline coronavirus carried by the cats. The disease is still terminal and the time of death is uncertain, but rarely lasts more than a year. Traditionally, only treatments aimed primarily at alleviating pain have been accepted.

There are a lot of introduction about GS-441524 on some domestic and foreign cat forum. At eight o'clock Jianwen interviewed a cat owner, her cat had been suffering from cat abdominal so more attention to the news of GS-441524, also published a lot of GS-441524, "at present domestic and foreign cats used more, the effect is very good. "

Redesavir (code-named GS-5734) is phosphorylated from GS-441524, "It's like a molecule of art. Relative to the Keli Zhi and other drugs, effective concentration is low, less toxic side effects, is the most recommended under the circumstances of a small molecule drug. As the researchers continue to modify, its activity is higher and its safety is better,"Zhao Yong excitedly told Jianwen at eight.".

The emergence of the diseases Ebola, Mers, and SARS has led to the development of drugs that inhibit the replication of RNA viruses, and Radzivir is considered one of the most promising drugs for emerging RNA viruses, the researchers believe that Radzivir could be further developed as a broad spectrum antiviral drug to treat viral infections with high mortality and significant outbreak potential.

In the wake of the new crown pneumonia outbreak, some previous studies have suggested that Civet may be one of the potential COVID-19 drugs. The current study does not confirm the efficacy of anti-hiv drugs, and the most promising drug may be Ridgisivir, the journal Science Online said Jan. 27.

On February 4, the Wuhan Institute of Virology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences announced that their research showed that Radzivir could effectively inhibit the infection of 2019-nCoV at the cellular level. Wuhan Institute of Virology also applied for a patent for this, causing a controversy.

One analysis suggests that the Wuhan Virus Institute's Patent Registration is Redesivir's use in treating the new coronavirus, and from an interest point of view, if granted, it could prevent patent holders from carrying the patents at inflated prices.

But patenting may not be so easy. Gilead has applied for or been awarded at least 100 patents related to ridgway since 2011. In 2016, Gilead applied for more patents in China and around the world for the use of Ridgway on coronaviruses, according to Gilead officials.

Patient First, the company's core concern is patients, and we don't want to get involved in patent disputes, Jilly, CEO  , said at a company conference Feb. 5 in response to the patent dispute.

According to a Gilead official release on Feb. 8, the company has reached an agreement with Ministry of Health of the People's Republic of China to provide the drugs needed for the study free of charge and to support the design and conduct of the study.

##Clinical trial and new crown disease which end first?

Right now, the epidemic is still spreading.

As of 24:00 on February 9,40,171 confirmed cases, 3,281 cured cases, 908 deaths and 23,589 suspected cases have been reported in China (except for Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan) . (information from the official website of the National Board of Health)

But the clinical trials led by the china-japan Friendship Hospital to assess the efficacy of Radzivir ended on April 27 and May 1, respectively. Unless there are extreme conditions in the trial, such as a large mortality risk, or a significant improvement in a large area, leading to early blindness, the results will not be known for more than two months.

Will patients be able to receive medications clinically through compassionate channels until Phase III is complete? The compassionate use of the drug was the process used in the American case to apply Ridgeville to patients.

"I don't think so, " a doctor in the ICU of a top-three hospital told Jianwen at eight o'clock. For clinical antiviral treatment, according to the Health Commission issued the fifth edition of the COVID-19, recommended smoking support plus antiviral treatment. He believes that before the clinical value of specific drugs have not been verified, do a good routine treatment measures, can also achieve good treatment results.

According to the FDA's official website, there are certain conditions for compassionate use:

The patient's condition is so critical that it affects his life
There is no comparable or better alternative therapy;
Failure to include patients in clinical trials;
The benefits to the patient outweigh the potential risks;
Compassionate use does not affect ongoing clinical trials.

The domestic situation is very different from that, wrote Wang Liming, a professor at the School of life sciences at Zhejiang University. "First, in China, the number of patients with npv pneumonia is so large that it is not particularly difficult to design and complete a human clinical trial. Second, the vast majority of patients with mild illness are treated successfully with traditional supportive therapy and antiviral therapy, and new therapies with unknown high risks are not needed. "

This also means that the only way for patients to use Radcivir is to be included in clinical trials.

In an interview, Zhang Wenhong, director of the infection department of Mount Hua Hospital and head of the Shanghai Medical Treatment Expert Group, said, "The most effective medicine is human immunity. What are we doctors doing? We are helping the patient to survive for two weeks. After that, his own antibodies are up and he has great power. "
